    <h1>Phone Etiquette</h1>
    <h2>Process Step by Step</h2>
    <ol>
        <br />
        <li><strong style="color: green">ANSWER</strong> the phone in <strong style="color: green">3</strong> <strong style="color: green">RINGS</strong> or less.
            <ol>
                <li>Take a deep breath.</li>
                <li>&ldquo;Smile&rdquo; over the phone &ndash; a positive attitude sets a pleasant tone for the entire call.</li>
                <li>Keep the customer LIVE.</li>
            </ol>
        </li>
        <br />
        <h1 style="background-color: green; border: thin black; border-radius: 5px">“Good [Afternoon], thank you for calling Tom Nehl Truck Company, [Jacksonville]. This is [Scott] in Parts. How may I help you?”</h1>
        <li><strong style="color: green">GREET</strong> the customer.</li>
        <br />
        <li><strong style="color: green">IDENTIFY </strong>yourself.</li>
        <ol>
            <li>Name</li>
            <li>Company Name</li>
            <li>Department</li>
        </ol>
        <br />
        <li><strong style="color: green">OFFER</strong></li>
        <br />
        <li><strong style="color: green">LISTEN</strong> and <strong style="color: green">CONFIRM</strong> the customer&rsquo;s need.
            <ol>
                <li>Ask open-ended questions to get a full picture of the situation.</li>
                <li>Ask for:
                    <ol>
                        <li>VIN/ESN</li>
                        <li>Model</li>
                        <li>Mileage/Hours</li>
                        <li>Etc.</li>
                    </ol>
                </li>
                <li>Summarize the customer&rsquo;s input to make sure you have a full grasp of the situation.</li>
                <li>If they reached the wrong department, gather information to do a warm transfer.</li>
            </ol>
        </li>
    </ol>
    <ul>
    </ul>
    <ol>
    </ol>
    <ol>
    </ol>
    <ol start="6">
        <br />
        <h1 style="background-color: green; border: thin black; border-radius: 5px">“May I have your name and phone number in case we’re disconnected?”</h1>

        <li><strong style="color: green">GATHER</strong> primary customer information immediately.
            <ol>
                <li>Contact Name</li>
                <li>Phone Number</li>
                <li>Company Name, Account Status</li>
                <li>If transferring, conference in the correct party. Let them know that you have the customer on the phone, explain the situation and make the hand off once contact is firmly made.</li>
            </ol>
        </li>
        <br />

        <li><strong style="color: green">TRY TO KEEP</strong> the customer <strong style="color: green">LIVE ON THE PHONE</strong> or gain their permission before putting them on hold!
            <ol>
                <li>If you need extra time to gather information, ask the customer for the best time to call them back. Follow up as promised.</li>
                <li>If able to research within a few minutes, offer value-added benefits of your company instead of &ldquo;dead-air.&rdquo;</li>
            </ol>
        </li>
        <br />

        <li><strong style="color: green">CONFIRM</strong> availability and <strong style="color: green">EXTEND</strong> the price.
            <ol>
                <li>If a part is not immediately available, communicate when and where it will be.
                    <ol>
                        <li>Interbranch?</li>
                        <li>PDC?</li>
                        <li>Direct Ship available?</li>
                        <li>Don&rsquo;t forget any freight, critical fees or restocking policies they need to know.</li>
                    </ol>
                    <li>Always extend the price &ndash; customers want to know the total due, not the breakdown.</li>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </li>
    </ol>
    <ul>
    </ul>
    <ol>
    </ol>
    <ol>
    </ol>
    <ol start="9">
        <br />

        <li><strong style="color: green">RECOMMEND</strong> the complete solution.
            <ol>
                <li>Are there any other associated parts the customer needs to complete the job?
                    <ol>
                        <li>Single injector --&gt; Offer a set of injectors, others should be ready to fail. Save on labor.</li>
                        <li>New DPF --&gt; Offer gaskets/clamps.</li>
                        <li>Hub --&gt; Offer spindle nut.</li>
                    </ol>
                    <li>Any other opportunities aside from the original request?</li>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </li>
    </ol>
    <ul>
    </ul>
    <ol>
    </ol>
    <ol start="10">
        <br />

        <li><strong style="color: green">ASK</strong> for the sale.</li>
    </ol>
    <p>&ldquo;Do you need us to deliver or can I put this on the customer holding shelf for you?&rdquo;</p>
    <ol start="11">
        <br />

        <li><strong style="color: green">OVERCOME RESISTANCE</strong> by stating <strong style="color: green">VALUE</strong> <strong style="color: green">ADDED</strong> <strong style="color: green">BENEFITS</strong>.</li>
    </ol>
    <p>Promote the company brand. Emphasize warranty advantages, etc.</p>
    <ol start="12">
        <br />

        <li><strong style="color: green">ASK</strong> for the sale a second time.</li>
    </ol>
    <p>Explore other options to help the customer accept your recommendation.</p>
    <ol start="13">
        <br />

        <li><strong style="color: green">THANK</strong> the customer and show appreciation.
            <ol>
                <li>Give the customer a way to get back in touch with you.</li>
                <li>&ldquo;Is there anything else I can assist you with today?&rdquo;</li>
            </ol>
        </li>
        <br />

        <li><strong style="color: green">FOLLOW THROUGH</strong>.
            <ol>
                <li>Do you what you say you&rsquo;re going to do!</li>
                <li>Be proactive. Ensure all questions are answered and no issues are left unresolved.</li>
            </ol>
        </li>
    </ol>
