    <h1>Phone References</h1>
    <h2>Process Step by Step</h2>
    <br />
    <img src="Images/digPhone.png" style="height: 500px; width: 900px" />
    <br />
    <h2>Dialing Calls</h2>
    <p>Pick up the handset and dial a number. Or, dial a number and press the <strong>Dial</strong> softkey.</p>
    <p><em>You do not need to dial a 9 or 1.</em></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <h2>Receiving Calls</h2>
    <p>Pick up the handset to answer a call. Or, press speaker to answer the call over speaker phone.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <h2>Redial</h2>
    <p>Press the Redial button to redial the last call you made.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <h2>Hold</h2>
    <p>During a call, press <strong>Hold</strong>. The line key flashes red.</p>
    <p>Press either the flashing line key or the <strong>Resume</strong> softkey to resume the call.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <h2>Transfer - Assisted</h2>
    <p>During a call, press the <strong>Transfer</strong> button or softkey. Enter a valid extension, and press the <strong>Dial</strong> softkey. A valid extension will show the contact information of that extension. When someone answers, inform them of the call to be transferred. Press the <strong>Transfer</strong> button or softkey again, and the transfer is completed.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <h2>Transfer &ndash; Unassisted/Blind</h2>
    <p>During a call, press the <strong>Transfer</strong> button or softkey. Enter a valid extension. A valid extension will show the contact information of that extension. Press the <strong>Transfer</strong> button or softkey again, and the transfer is completed.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <h2>Three Way Calling</h2>
    <p>During a call, press the <strong>Conference</strong> softkey. Make a call, or <strong>Resume</strong> another existing call. Press <strong>Conference</strong> again to connect all participants. To end the conference and put both calls on hold, press the <strong>Split</strong> softkey on either call.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <h2>Park</h2>
    <p>During a call, press the <strong>Park</strong> softkey. This will place the call on a parked extension (101, 102, 103, etc.). You may answer this call from any phone by dialing the parked extension number.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <h2>Voicemail</h2>
    <p>The message waiting indicator will blink red when you have new voicemails. Press the <strong>Voicemail</strong> button to display your voicemail inbox. Any message with an asterisk (<strong>*</strong>) has not been played. To listen to a message, select it and press the <strong>Play</strong> softkey.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <h2>Conference Calls</h2>
    <p>There are phone conference rooms available to use on extensions <strong>800</strong> and <strong>801</strong>. You may dial these extensions from any phone to connect, or transfer an external caller to the conference room extension you wish to use.</p>
